t package outside of the library package. I should look into dependencies and maybe use JUnit assertions instead of AssertJ. I wonder if the MicroProfile config API is transitive. I also need to check if tests are in an unnamed module or if I should specify module/native details. It's a bit of a puzzle, but I’ll sort it out!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating configuration setup**\\n\\nI’m considering if ConfigBuilder.build may only load filter services. I’ll utilize `assertArrayEquals` for object arrays that override equals in custom types. Simpler comparisons could leverage Arrays.stream. Assertions are essential, along with ensuring all classes are publicly accessible. I should delete any placeholders and use JUnit 5. I’ll also need to check for compliance with checkstyle, especially concerning class naming. There might be issues with MicroProfile Config handling arrays, and I should verify dynamic reflection requirements for native images and tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering metadata and resources**\\n\\nI'm thinking that if there are no metadata resources, running native might be an issue. I shouldn’t be editing anything, but I do need to write. Maybe I could remove placeholders using a bash command like `rm`, so I can write a new one and remove the old. This approach makes sense, as it's a straightforward way to ensure everything is organized and updated correctly without complicated edits.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8ib0PHivZPLpVHTFMHLkaQzI|fc_0dcd6b818b603e36016a236fa96cd48196b9ebf9f74bf9f1a3", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.helidon.config/helidon-config-mp/4.3.4/src/test/java/io_helidon_config/helidon_config_mp/MpConfigImplTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_helidon_config.helidon_config_mp;\n\nimport java.util.LinkedHashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.Optional;\n\nimport io.helidon.config.mp.MpConfigSources;\n\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.config.Config;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.config.spi.ConfigProviderResolver;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.config.spi.Converter;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertArrayEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\npublic class MpConfigImplTest {\n    @Test\n    void convertsValuesWithImplicitStaticMethodAndStringConstructor() {\n        Config config = config(Map.of(\n                \"method.values\", \"alpha,beta\",\n                \"constructor.values.0\", \"gamma\",\n                \"constructor.values.1\", \"delta\"));\n\n        MethodBasedValue[] methodValues = config.getValue(\"method.values\", MethodBasedValue[].class);\n        Optional<ConstructorBasedValue[]> constructorValues = config.getOptionalValue(\n                \"constructor.values\",\n                ConstructorBasedValue[].class);\n\n        assertArrayEquals(new MethodBasedValue[] {new MethodBasedValue(\"method:alpha\"),\n                new MethodBasedValue(\"method:beta\")}, methodValues);\n        assertTrue(constructorValues.isPresent());\n        assertArrayEquals(new ConstructorBasedValue[] {new ConstructorBasedValue(\"gamma\"),\n                new ConstructorBasedValue(\"delta\")}, constructorValues.get());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void exposesArrayConverterForImplicitComponentConverters() {\n        Config config = config(Map.of());\n\n        Converter<MethodBasedValue[]> converter = config.getConverter(MethodBasedValue[].class).orElseThrow();\n        MethodBasedValue[] converted = converter.convert(\"first,second\");\n\n        assertArrayEquals(new MethodBasedValue[] {new MethodBasedValue(\"method:first\"),\n                new MethodBasedValue(\"method:second\")}, converted);\n    }\n\n    private static Config config(Map<String, String> values) {\n        return ConfigProviderResolver.instance()\n                .getBuilder()\n                .withSources(MpConfigSources.create(\"test-values\", new LinkedHashMap<>(values)))\n                .build();\n    }\n\n    public static final class MethodBasedValue {\n        private final String value;\n\n        private MethodBasedValue(String value) {\n            this.value = value;\n        }\n\n        public static MethodBasedValue of(String value) {\n            return new MethodBasedValue(\"method:\" + value);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean equals(Object other) {\n            if (this == other) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            if (!(other instanceof MethodBasedValue that)) {\n                return false;\n            }\n            return value.equals(that.value);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int hashCode() {\n            return value.hashCode();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class ConstructorBasedValue {\n        private final String value;\n\n        public ConstructorBasedValue(String value) {\n            this.value = \"constructor:\" + value;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean equals(Object other) {\n            if (this == other) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            if (!(other instanceof ConstructorBasedValue that)) {\n                return false;\n            }\n            return value.equals(that.value);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int hashCode() {\n            return value.hashCode();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1536, "output": 2418, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31090, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "time